{
  "texts": [
    "introduced the QANet model in 2018, with a performance of 76.2% exact match and 84.6% F1-Score, within a shorter computational time of 3 hours [9].",
    "As QA systems evolve, in 2019 Wei Yang et al.",
    "applied finetuning methods with data augmentation techniques, achieving remarkable results with a modified BERT-Base model of 49.2% for exact match and 65.4% for F1-Score [10].",
    "Colin Raffel et al.",
    "introduced the Text-to-Text Transfer Transformer (T5), with impressive performance of 63.3% for exact match, 94.1% for F1 score, and a peak accuracy of 93.8%, albeit with an increased number of parameters of 11 billion [11]."
  ]
}